267
0:11:08.26,000 --> 0:11:11,000
So that's one more element for this continuity.

268
0:11:11.26,000 --> 0:11:13,000
And the final thing

269
0:11:13.26,000 --> 0:11:15,000
is that there is a very tight coupling

270
0:11:15.26,000 --> 0:11:19,000
between the regulation of our body within the brain

271
0:11:19.26,000 --> 0:11:21,000
and the body itself,

272
0:11:21.26,000 --> 0:11:24,000
unlike any other coupling.

273
0:11:24.26,000 --> 0:11:26,000
So for example, I'm making images of you,

274
0:11:26.26,000 --> 0:11:29,000
but there's no physiological bond

275
0:11:29.26,000 --> 0:11:32,000
between the images I have of you as an audience

276
0:11:32.26,000 --> 0:11:34,000
and my brain.

277
0:11:34.26,000 --> 0:11:38,000
However, there is a close, permanently maintained bond

278
0:11:38.26,000 --> 0:11:41,000
between the body regulating parts of my brain

279
0:11:41.26,000 --> 0:11:43,000
and my own body.

280
0:11:43.26,000 --> 0:11:46,000
So here's how it looks. Look at the region there.

281
0:11:46.26,000 --> 0:11:49,000
There is the brain stem in between the cerebral cortex

282
0:11:49.26,000 --> 0:11:51,000
